; **********************************************************************************
; Negative test for card maize-37, cross-ref maize-52: label_tokenizer used to fall
; out of its EOF loop with only the name child added when EOF arrived right after
; the name was flushed into label_state::value, handing label_compiler a 1-child
; node that crashed dereferencing past tree.value.end(). mazm must now reject the
; truncation with a clean diagnostic instead.
; The test harness treats this file as ExpectAsmError: it passes when assembly fails.
; This file intentionally ends immediately after the label's name: EOF must land
; there, with no value token at all, for the truncation to actually reproduce.
; **********************************************************************************

LABEL truncated_label
